<br>
I was asked if I would like to join another guild on a raid for a piece of my mage epic.  The epic item is the crown of elemental mastery, and the item is located on the 7th isle in the Plane of Sky.  There will be about 8 groups going up to chase crowns.  This will be scheduled a weeklong, work days only.  I personally think with any amount of luck, it will only require 2-3 days.  Anyway, it will cost about 3K per group, which I will be funding our group, it will not cost the people that go with me anything.  They recommended that I have 5 others 54+.  I told them they we are a small guild and didn’t have many above 50.  So, I would like to have some volunteers to pledge their lives to my quest.  By design, we will all die each day and have our bodies summoned to the camp spot.  Now, I must warn any that wish to come.  You will most likely die at least once.  As in all raids, expect to die, and fight to live.  I can not guaranty any loot or experience, but being a plane, it should have some stuff.  These raids will be done 6:30 pacific time, and we will not be picking up any LFGs, unless they are known by the leaders of each group.<br>
<br>
Now, I am hoping for:<br>
A Healer *cough* Aaryl or Shaune *cough*<br>
A Bard *cough* Harmonae *cough*<br>
A Tank *cough* Mandi *cough*<br>
A Rogue  (oh, you know who are by now)<br>
And possibly a Pally (possibly a bald pally) or a nice ranger (nal) or a non tagged druid (Xeen)<br>
<br>
I am sorry for being so specific, but for anyone below 50 is Very dangerous, and you can’t get into the planes until 46.<br>
<br>
I would be most grateful for any help.  The plan is for the first week of April.<br>
<br>
Best Regards,<br>
<br>
Jonan Elementruler<br>
Level 52 Elementalist<br>
Elder of the Aegis Wolves<br>
